<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-07-22T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-07-22T04:00:00-05:00" n="651" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d651">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">711.932/7–2248: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-07-22T18:00:00+09:00">July 22, 1948—6
                            p.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 22—8:04 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1347. ReEmbtel 1346, July 22. Foreign Minister has decided Senate reservation
                        cannot be submitted present session Legislative Yuan because Executive Yuan
                        approval, which must be obtained at special meeting, cannot be gotten prior
                        adjournment Legislative Yuan tomorrow.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>